---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="AI Marking">
  <h1>AI Marking</h1>
  <p class="lede muted">
    REREVI builds a ready-made prompt for every question. Paste it into any AI —
    ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok — together with your answer, and it marks you
    against <em>our</em> mark scheme and gives feedback. It's an <strong>approximate</strong>
    practice mark, not an official Eduqas result.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>How to use it</h3>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Generate a paper or look up a question.</li>
      <li>Hit <strong>📋 Copy AI prompt</strong> (per question) or <strong>Copy whole-paper AI prompt</strong>.</li>
      <li>Paste it into your AI of choice, then paste your answer where it says <code>{'{paste your answer here}'}</code>.</li>
      <li>Read the band, mark, strengths and "to reach the next band" feedback.</li>
      <li>Back on REREVI, choose <em>AI marking</em> in the scorer and record the mark to track it.</li>
    </ol>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:0.6rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="/generator" class="btn btn-primary">Generate a paper →</a>
      <a href="/question-lookup" class="btn">Look up a question</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:1rem;">
    <h3>Why it's reliable-ish</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Self-contained:</strong> the prompt carries the full mark scheme inline, so the AI doesn't need anything else.</li>
      <li><strong>Constrained:</strong> it's told to mark <em>only</em> against the scheme and use a fixed output format — less "grading on vibes".</li>
      <li><strong>Honest:</strong> every prompt states the mark is approximate.</li>
      <li><strong>Evaluation-aware:</strong> for (d) parts it specifically checks for balance, reasoning and a justified conclusion — where marks are usually lost.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="notice notice-warn">
      AIs can still be too generous or too harsh. Use it to find <em>gaps</em>, then
      confirm borderline marks against the mark scheme yourself.
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .lede { font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 60ch; }
  .steps, ul { color: var(--text); }
  .steps li, ul li { margin: 0.4rem 0; }
  h3 { margin-top: 0; }
  .card + .card { margin-top: 1rem; }
</style>
